<br>
About a year ago, I saw my old guild leader and I sent him a tell. He did not know who I was. We had been through so much together, including Berber's death, and we even spoke on the phone a few times. It was hard to read his reply to my friendly greeting. &quot;Do I know you?&quot; He had said. Because it was not the original Thundax.<br>
<br>
I would sooner delete Radjan than sell her (not that she'd sell for much money, mind you). I know that Radjan is so much a part of who I am. She is an extension of myself. And yes, I answer to &quot;Radjan&quot; as much as I answer to &quot;Anne.&quot;<br>
<br>
It is not the inability of the purchaser to play the e-Bay'd character that bothers me. It is the loss of the character's soul when it's sold. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.powersoffate.com/Graphics/Radjan3.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roshamon>Roshamon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Bok Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/7/02 1:55:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=644.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~ljrichq34/zzz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What to do when your MT ebays ..</span><hr size=1> At the risk of a thread hijack, I want to add to Radjan's eloquent words.  It comes down to the way people perceive their avatars.  Some people see it as an extension of themselves, while others see the toon in a third person sense.  Neither is right nor wrong, just different.  That is where the issues of ebay (disregarding the legal problems ever present in the eula), disrupt the community as a whole.  <br>
<br>
For those like myself, Radjan, and others, who seek out the &quot;soul&quot; within the avatar, an ebayed character of a close friend makes you feel uneasy, almost betrayed.  Someone who you shared moments with, funny, poignant, bittersweet, and even angry moments, has been wiped of all memory and bodysnatched.  The new person could be one of the sweetest men/women on the planet, but that person would have to work twice as hard in the eyes of the avatar's former peers.<br>
<br>
The stories are legendary of the ebayed character (Burned Woods anyone?).  I remember the Mage friend of Teg I mentioned in my earlier post.  Level 50 Magician, walking around Solusek B with absolutely no clue.  Seconds later, he's been taken out by a spider.  Again, its possible, and as the game gets older, probable that those who buy characters are good players all around, but if its known that the character is ebayed, the buyer has to work twice as hard to be considered capable.<br>
<br>
It may be worth it to the seller, but is it really worth it to a new player to take on so many disadvantages so early on? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qutsemnie>Qutsemnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tolapumj wanna-be</span><br>  Posts: 273<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(11/7/02 2:31:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=644.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What to do when your MT ebays ..</span><hr size=1> &quot;Some people see it as an extension of themselves, while others see the toon in a third person sense. Neither is right nor wrong&quot;<br>
<br>
Generally the only &quot;person&quot; i know of other people i know from online are their toon.  Theres no question that its sad to see a close friend in game and them not know who you are because your friend ebayed.  Think it just makes acute how transient this all is.<br>
<br>
as for your MA leaving.  wasnt caused by ebay.  dont think 500 bucks has ever enticed anyone to leave the game.  (btw 3000 dollars and you can cause me to leave =)   Its a way to buy something nice *after* you decided to leave.   There are a few that milk it and cycle characters etc.  But thats not the general populace.  Most just decide the day has come to when they should take a bow and say goodnite.<br>
